03/01/2003
SKOPJE, Macedonia -- President Boris Trajkovski has initiated a regional roundtable with his counterparts in Albania, Croatia, Bosnia and Herzegovina and Yugoslavia, aimed at promoting and co-ordinating their EU entry efforts, his spokesperson announced Thursday (2 January). In a recent joint letter to the EU, the five presidents sought firmer commitments from the Union in regards to their integration efforts. Albanian President Alfred Moisiu says he supports the initiative and agreed that the summit could take place in mid-January. (MIA, Tanjug, A1 TV - 02/03/01)
